<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Pleuraphis</i> <i>jamesii</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Achnatherum</i> <i>hymenoides</i>, <i>Bouteloua</i> <i>eriopoda</i>, <i>Bouteloua</i> <i>gracilis</i>, <i>Elymus</i> <i>elymoides</i>, <i>Muhlenbergia</i> <i>porteri</i> and <i>Scleropogon</i> <i>brevifolius</i>. Emergent trees and shrubs may be present at low cover, including trees <i>Yucca</i> <i>brevifolia</i> and shrubs:<i>Artemisia</i> <i>tridentata</i>, <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>acanthocarpa</i>, <i>Ephedra</i> <i>nevadensis</i>, <i>Ephedra</i> <i>viridis</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>wrightii</i>, <i>Gutierrezia</i> <i>microcephala</i>, <i>Menodora</i> <i>spinescens</i> and <i>Sphaeralcea</i> <i>ambigua</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Pleuraphis jamesii</i> > 2% absolute cover in the herbaceous layer; herbaceous cover exceeds tree or shrub cover (Thomas et al. 2004).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Upper bajadas, gentle to moderately steep slopes, mesas, and valleys. Soils range from deep, coarse sandy to gravelly or rocky igneous soils.  </div>
</div>

        
