<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Pleuraphis jamesii </i>is resistant to grazing and fire. It has a lower stature and is more strongly rhizomatous than <i>P. rigida</i>. Rhizome buds sprout following fire, and plants re-establish within 2 years. In some parts of its range, with repeat burns, <i>P. jamesii </i>spreads at the expense of shrubs (Simonin 2000c, M. Brooks, pers. comm. 2007). It appears not as tolerant of grazing within California, the drier parts of its range, where grazing has reduced the extent of the alliance.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
